Police Minister Bheki Cele has on Thursday visited the Browns Farm community over crime-related incidents and police interventions. This comes after the minister was briefed at Nyanga police station in Cape Town on Wednesday, by SAPS management following a shooting incident that left four people dead, including two children, aged 12 and 13. The fifth victim injured in the incident is still recovering in hospital. It is alleged that they were shot dead by three armed men while sitting in a Toyota Avanza in the Browns Farm informal settlement in Nyanga. The suspects fled the scene and no arrests have been made. The motive for the attack is yet to be determined. -TNA Reporter